<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1727,2034]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,303,1727,1753]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Description.</emphasis>
Body length: É—, 
<quantity box="[502,589,1728,1754]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="7.8">7.8mm</quantity>
. Body colour generally dark brown to blackish brown. Anteclypeus with pair of black spots and stout setae apically (
<figureCitation box="[664,734,1768,1794]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="20.[151,255,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[230,1360,219,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[205,1384,194,1857]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 7. Cyrta spinosa sp. n. A, face; B, head and thorax, dorsal view; C, male genital capsule, lateral view; D, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style and connective, dorsal view; G, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182583/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[719,734,1768,1794]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
A); vertex distincly concave medially forming a weak ridge near apical margin in dorsal lview (
<figureCitation box="[579,652,1808,1834]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="20.[151,255,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[230,1360,219,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[205,1384,194,1857]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 7. Cyrta spinosa sp. n. A, face; B, head and thorax, dorsal view; C, male genital capsule, lateral view; D, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style and connective, dorsal view; G, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182583/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[636,652,1808,1834]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Head and thorax with short yellow setae; scutellum with very long tufts of yellow hairlike setae basally and black hairlike setae apically (
<figureCitation box="[1033,1104,1848,1874]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="20.[151,255,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[230,1360,219,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[205,1384,194,1857]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 7. Cyrta spinosa sp. n. A, face; B, head and thorax, dorsal view; C, male genital capsule, lateral view; D, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style and connective, dorsal view; G, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182583/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[1088,1104,1848,1874]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1727,2034]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Male pygofer rounded distally, with very dense short to long macrosetae and very short setae (
<figureCitation box="[1328,1401,1888,1914]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="20.[151,255,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[230,1360,219,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[205,1384,194,1857]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 7. Cyrta spinosa sp. n. A, face; B, head and thorax, dorsal view; C, male genital capsule, lateral view; D, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style and connective, dorsal view; G, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182583/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[1385,1401,1888,1914]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
C). Valve broad basally, angularly developed distally; subgenital plate extending not beyond to apex of pygofer side, with dense setae from base to apex (
<figureCitation box="[640,711,1968,1994]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="20.[151,255,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[230,1360,219,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[205,1384,194,1857]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 7. Cyrta spinosa sp. n. A, face; B, head and thorax, dorsal view; C, male genital capsule, lateral view; D, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style and connective, dorsal view; G, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182583/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[695,711,1968,1994]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
D). Aedeagus very boad subbasally in both lateral and ventral view; shaft with several stout lateral spines (
<figureCitation box="[671,745,2008,2034]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="20.[151,255,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[230,1360,219,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[205,1384,194,1857]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 7. Cyrta spinosa sp. n. A, face; B, head and thorax, dorsal view; C, male genital capsule, lateral view; D, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style and connective, dorsal view; G, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182583/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Figs 
<number box="[730,745,2008,2034]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
E, G).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
