, Liu Shengli. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,338,191,217]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name of this species is derived from the spines on the aedeagus. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,318,231,257]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from all other species of the genus by its unique aedeagus which is very broad subbasally in both lateral and ventral view with several lateral spines on the shaft (
<figureCitation box="[1362,1436,272,298]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="20.[151,255,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[230,1360,219,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[205,1384,194,1857]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 7. Cyrta spinosa sp. n. A, face; B, head and thorax, dorsal view; C, male genital capsule, lateral view; D, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; E, aedeagus, ventral view; F, style and connective, dorsal view; G, style, connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/182583/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Figs 
<number box="[1421,1436,272,298]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
E, G).
</paragraph>
